{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "Document Relevance.",
    "The relevance between the query 𝑞 and a document 𝑑 is quantified by the probability of generating its corresponding DocID 𝑑 ′ given 𝑞.",
    "This is computed as:R (𝑞, 𝑑) = 𝑃 (𝑑 ′ |𝑞; 𝜃) = 𝑇 𝑖=1 𝑃 (𝑑 ′ 𝑖 | 𝑑 ′ <𝑖, 𝑞; 𝜃),(6)where 𝑇 is the length of the DocID 𝑑 ′ in tokens, 𝑑 ′ 𝑖 is the token at position 𝑖, and 𝑑 ′ <𝑖 denotes the sequence of tokens generated before position 𝑖.",
    "The constrained beam search produces a ranked list of top-𝑘 DocIDs {𝑑 ′ (1), 𝑑 ′(2),..., 𝑑 ′(𝑘) } based on their generation probabilities {R (𝑞, 𝑑 (1)), R (𝑞, 𝑑 (2)),..., R (𝑞, 𝑑 (𝑘))}.",
    "The corresponding documents {𝑑 (1), 𝑑 (2),..., 𝑑 (𝑘) } are then considered the most relevant to the query 𝑞.Model Optimization."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
